description: This dashboard shows live load test metrics provided by JMeter, updated bars charts.

targets.query:
current = from(bucket: v.bucket)
  |> range(start: time(v: ${current_startTime}), stop: time(v: ${current_endTime}))
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "requestsRaw")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "responseTime")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["testName"] == "${app}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["runId"] == "${testTitle}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["samplerType"] == "${type}")
  |> keep(columns:["_field","_value"])
  |> median()
  |> set(key: "Metric", value: "Median response time")
  |> rename(columns: {"_value": "Current"})

baseline = from(bucket: v.bucket)
  |> range(start: time(v: ${baseline_startTime}), stop: time(v: ${baseline_endTime}))
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "requestsRaw")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "responseTime")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["testName"] == "${app}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["runId"] == "${baseline_testTitle}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["samplerType"] == "${type}")
  |> keep(columns:["_field","_value"])
  |> median()
  |> set(key: "Metric", value: "Median response time")
  |> rename(columns: {"_value": "Baseline"})

join(tables: {t1: current, t2: baseline}, on: ["Metric"])

current = from(bucket: v.bucket)
  |> range(start: time(v: ${current_startTime}), stop: time(v: ${current_endTime}))
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "requestsRaw")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "count")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["samplerType"] == "request")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["testName"] == "${app}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["runId"] == "${testTitle}")
  |> group(columns: ["testName", "result"])
  |> sum()
  |> toFloat()
  |> pivot(rowKey: ["testName"], columnKey: ["result"], valueColumn: "_value")
  |> map(fn: (r) => ({ r with all: if exists r.fail then (r.fail + r.pass) else r.pass }))
  |> map(fn: (r) => ({ r with errors: if exists r.fail then (r.fail/r.all*100.0) else 0.0 }))
  |> keep(columns: ["errors"])
  |> rename(columns: {"errors": "Current"})
  |> set(key: "Metric", value: "Errors,%")

list.definition:
from(bucket: v.bucket)
  |> range(start: 0, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "virtualUsers")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "maxActiveThreads")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["testName"] == "${app}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["runId"] == "${testTitle}")
  |> keep(columns: ["_time"])
  |> min(column: "_time")
  |> map(fn: (r) => ({ r with _time: string(v: r._time)}))
